Ventral chaetotaxy. Th. I−III without chaetae. Ventral tube with 3+3 apical chaetae, without lateral chaetae. Abd. II with 4+4 chaetae; Abd. III with 5+5 chaetae. Furcula well developed with 6 chaetae on each dens; mucro reduced, unilobed, three times shorter than dens (
Fig. 24
